Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and quarter @zucchini{1}(trimmed and quartered lengthwise); cut crosswise into
1/2-inch-thick pieces. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}(zested and quartered).

Toss zucchini and @grape tomatoes{4%oz} on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of
@cooking oil{drizzle}, half the @garlic powder{1%tsp} (you'll use the rest later),
a pinch of @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until tender and
lightly browned, ~{12-14%minutes}.

Meanwhile, melt @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in a large pan over
medium heat. Add @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup} and cook, stirring constantly, until
golden brown, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #small bowl{} and stir in a pinch of salt, pepper,
and as much lemon zest as you like. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp} in pan used for panko over medium heat. Add
@orzo pasta{8%oz} and cook, stirring, until orzo is toasted and golden,
~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in @Vidalia onion paste{1/2%oz}, remaining garlic powder, and 2 cups
@water{2%cups} (4 cups for 4 servings). Bring to a boil, then reduce to a
low simmer. Simmer, stirring occasionally, until orzo is al dente, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Stir in @cream sauce base{4%oz} and cook, stirring occasionally, until liquid has
reduced and orzotto is creamy, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from heat; stir in half the roasted zucchini and tomatoes and
@butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4). Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

> Orzotto should be the consistency of risotto! If it seems too thick, stir in a
> splash of water.

== Salad ==

In a #large bowl{}, whisk together @olive oil{1%tbsp}, @sugar{1/2%tsp}, juice from
one lemon wedge, a pinch of @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{} (for 4 servings, use
2 TBSP olive oil, 1 tsp sugar, and juice from two wedges).

Add @arugula{2%oz} and @sliced almonds{1/2%oz}; toss to coat.

== To Serve ==

Divide orzotto between shallow plates; divide salad between separate bowls.
Top orzotto with remaining roasted zucchini and tomatoes and panko. Serve with
remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Fish is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.